A '''probability experiment''' is a [[situation]] where [[chance]] affects the [[outcome]] (the [[wikt:result|result]] of an experiment).  If the experiment can only have two outcomes, it is named [[Bernoulli trial]]. A [[coin]] flip is a probability experiment because [[chance]] affects whether a [[coin]] will land [[head|heads]] or [[tail|tails]] when it is flipped.

