'''Nth root''' of a [[number]] ''r'' is a number which, if [[multiplication|multiplied]] by itself ''n'' times, makes ''r''. You could also say that it is a number ''k'' for which the [[equation]] is true: :<math>k^n=r</math> (for meaning of <math>k^n</math>, read [[exponentiation]].)
We write it like this: <math>\sqrt[n]{r}</math>. {{math-stub}}
