[[Category:Mathematics]]

'''Real analysis''' is an area of [[mathematics]] that deals with [[set]]s and [[sequence]]s of [[real number]]s, as well as [[Function (mathematics)|functions]] of one or more [[real variable]]s. As one of the main branches of [[analysis]], it can be seen as a subset of [[complex analysis]].  Many results in real analysis are [[special case]]s of results in complex analysis.


