'''Homotopies''' are studied in a branch of [[mathematics]] known as [[Algebraic Topology]]. A homotopy is a [[wikt:deformation|deformation]] (change of [[form]]) of one thing into another without [[cutting]] it. For example, if we imagine a stretchy object, then all the shapes we can stretch or twist it into are "[[Homotopy equivalence|homotopy equivalent]]". One famous example is the homotopy equivalence of a [[coffee cup]] and a [[donut]]. To a [[topologist]], these two shapes are the same.

